1
00:00:01,490 --> 00:00:16,180
The Lord is really good, isn't he? Amen. He was really good to us last Monday. God has given me a passion for a game without the ability to play it.

2
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:29,960
I've become a real lover of this silly game of golf, but I can't play it. But I can appreciate those who can.

3
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:36,160
And the Lord was good and gave us a ringer on the Fullerton First Baptist team

4
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:39,100
in the Emery Campbell Golf Tournament.

5
00:00:39,880 --> 00:00:45,900
And it's been a personal mission of mine to eventually get up there and place in that tournament

6
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:48,320
because this was Emery's church.

7
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:54,360
And it seemed disgraceful that Fullerton would not someday rise to the occasion

8
00:00:54,360 --> 00:00:56,700
and lead and win.

9
00:00:56,700 --> 00:01:00,320
And last Monday, we did. Praise the Lord.

10
00:01:05,290 --> 00:01:10,650
We were on a mission, Michael Dismuke and Ed Mueller, Jeff Templeton and myself bringing up the rear.

11
00:01:11,550 --> 00:01:15,170
We actually all had to contribute something, so it was legitimate.

12
00:01:15,350 --> 00:01:21,790
We were actually a team, but let's be honest, our professional Jeff Templeton carried the day,

13
00:01:22,330 --> 00:01:27,390
and it was poetic to watch him play, and it was really fun.

14
00:01:27,390 --> 00:01:35,910
I want to thank Merle Dean for putting together two teams to make the bid for the summit, if you will, and one of them made it.

15
00:01:36,290 --> 00:01:42,190
So, praise the Lord, we are now on the plaque forever as the winners in the Emery Campbell Golf Tournament.

16
00:01:42,710 --> 00:01:46,070
So, congratulate those players. We're happy to share that good news.

17
00:01:46,890 --> 00:01:54,700
Well, you may have heard the story about the little boy with two quarters that is walking near the storm drain.

18
00:01:54,700 --> 00:02:00,950
and inadvertently, one of the coins made it into the grate

19
00:02:00,950 --> 00:02:05,890
and through and splashed at the bottom of the storm sewer.

20
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:10,060
And as he was taking those coins to church,

21
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:14,240
he said, well, Lord, there went your coin

22
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:21,050
because he'd rather buy ice cream with the other.

23
00:02:21,050 --> 00:02:24,390
And obviously, the Lord's coin went to the bottom.

24
00:02:25,130 --> 00:02:28,210
Friends, sometimes that can be our approach, isn't it, to our giving?

25
00:02:28,210 --> 00:02:36,220
Lord, I want this, and I want to give you that, and whoops, this didn't happen, so I guess that was your portion.

26
00:02:37,070 --> 00:02:38,810
We still want to do what we want to do.

27
00:02:39,370 --> 00:02:45,610
As we summarize where we've been in this series on stewardship, I'd like just to share a few things for on the screen

28
00:02:45,610 --> 00:02:50,710
as a summary of kind of where we've been as it leads us into where we're going today.

29
00:02:51,510 --> 00:02:56,100
Seven benefits to giving in our lives.

30
00:02:56,100 --> 00:03:01,270
The first one is that giving makes us more like God.

31
00:03:01,830 --> 00:03:06,630
We've explored that in different ways, but God's heart is to give.

32
00:03:07,070 --> 00:03:12,270
And as we desire to be made more like Jesus Christ, that our character is formed like His,

33
00:03:12,610 --> 00:03:17,310
as we give, we become more like the character of God our Father.

34
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:21,980
Giving will draw you closer to God.

35
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:24,680
God calls us to be givers.

36
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:31,540
And our giving will make us more in touch with His heart and draw us closer to the Lord.

37
00:03:33,070 --> 00:03:39,970
Giving breaks, as we've talked about, the grip that our hearts can have for material things.

38
00:03:40,150 --> 00:03:50,720
It can break our materialism by keeping us soft and keeping us healthy in terms of a perspective of what's really important in the world.

39
00:03:52,490 --> 00:03:54,570
Giving will strengthen our faith

40
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:57,720
because we're going to have to trust the Lord

41
00:03:57,720 --> 00:04:00,120
if we're going to give Him a significant portion

42
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:02,500
of what He's already given to us.

43
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,440
It strengthens our faith.

44
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:07,230
It's an investment for eternity.

45
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:10,160
An investment for eternity.

46
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:15,920
It will bless you in return as you give.

47
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:18,800
We talked about the measure in which you give

48
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,820
is the measure it's given back to you.

49
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:22,780
It blesses you.

50
00:04:22,780 --> 00:04:26,500
And finally, giving will simply make you happy.

51
00:04:27,420 --> 00:04:32,460
You will give with cheerfulness as God begins to mold your heart in those directions.

52
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:34,340
It will make you happy.

53
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,960
And with those benefits of giving to the Lord,

54
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:41,020
I just want to challenge us, who can refuse to be generous

55
00:04:41,020 --> 00:04:45,080
with the things that God has given us as we give back to Him?

56
00:04:46,110 --> 00:04:50,250
Who could desire to not acquire these things?

57
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:53,400
I want to be about those things.

58
00:04:54,820 --> 00:05:00,620
And I want us all to be givers with joy from our hearts.

59
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:07,140
There's two more passages I want us to reflect on as we conclude this series.

60
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:11,040
And the first one is in Matthew 6.21.

61
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:15,100
And it's the topic of the issue of treasure.

62
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:19,860
A short verse, but Jesus said it poignantly,

63
00:05:19,860 --> 00:05:25,800
Wherever your treasure is, there your heart and thoughts will be also.

64
00:05:26,980 --> 00:05:32,140
Where your treasure is, there your hearts and thoughts will be also.

65
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:38,000
Jesus said that because we are tied to our treasure.

66
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:41,960
We are stuck to our stuff.

67
00:05:43,140 --> 00:05:45,580
And we grasp at our goods.

68
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:50,780
Where our treasure is, that is where our heart is.

69
00:05:50,780 --> 00:05:54,180
Where our treasure is, there are our thoughts.

70
00:05:54,540 --> 00:06:00,080
Where our treasure is, that determines what consumes our life and our soul.

71
00:06:02,630 --> 00:06:08,440
Where you put your treasure is where your heart will follow eventually.

72
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:12,360
It always happens this way.

73
00:06:13,350 --> 00:06:15,610
As creatures, we're tied to our treasure.

74
00:06:16,350 --> 00:06:18,930
One of the key ways that we can worship the Lord

75
00:06:18,930 --> 00:06:24,170
and place our hearts in heaven is to give to heaven.

76
00:06:24,330 --> 00:06:29,220
because our hearts will follow where our treasure is.

77
00:06:31,060 --> 00:06:33,160
Where you put your treasure is where your heart is.

78
00:06:33,420 --> 00:06:38,320
The Apostle Paul wrote this, I think, knowing underneath this principle.

79
00:06:38,660 --> 00:06:40,640
He wrote in 1 Corinthians 16,

80
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:47,240
On every Lord's Day, each of you should put aside some amount of money

81
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:52,660
in relation to what you have earned and save it for this offering.

82
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:57,580
Paul was instructing the Corinthians in this chapter,

83
00:06:58,570 --> 00:07:01,550
these Corinthian Christians, to be very intentional

84
00:07:01,550 --> 00:07:04,450
about what their offering would be.

85
00:07:04,450 --> 00:07:09,450
And he challenges each person to set aside money,

86
00:07:09,690 --> 00:07:14,650
intentionally, all of them, with purpose and forethought.

87
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:19,790
Later in 2 Corinthians 9, he encourages them this way,

88
00:07:21,540 --> 00:07:25,780
You must each make up your mind as to how much you should give.

89
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:29,400
Don't give reluctantly or in response to pressure,

90
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:34,800
for God loves the person who gives cheerfully, cheerfully.

91
00:07:36,430 --> 00:07:41,250
Once again, we see an admonition to be intentional with our giving.

92
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:47,420
Friends, today we are asking as we give our offering after this message

93
00:07:47,420 --> 00:07:51,740
that we might be intentional as we purpose in our hearts

94
00:07:51,740 --> 00:07:53,160
what we're going to give,

95
00:07:53,860 --> 00:07:55,680
that we might begin in our process

96
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,520
of looking at ministry for next year,

97
00:07:57,860 --> 00:07:59,600
know where we stand.

98
00:08:00,510 --> 00:08:03,310
We want us to decide before we get here

99
00:08:03,310 --> 00:08:05,950
and be purposeful in our giving.

100
00:08:06,770 --> 00:08:07,110
Why?

101
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,720
Because where I put my treasure,

102
00:08:10,300 --> 00:08:12,500
my heart will go there eventually.

103
00:08:13,540 --> 00:08:15,980
We must be intentional in our worship.

104
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:21,120
We really don't often think

105
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:24,140
about what we're doing with our giving sometimes.

106
00:08:26,690 --> 00:08:31,390
I'd like for us to, for a moment, to reflect on the experience of the checkout counter.

107
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:39,120
I'm often there, two small kids.

108
00:08:40,420 --> 00:08:46,880
The racks are full of things that you didn't intend to go into the store to buy, did you?

109
00:08:47,890 --> 00:08:51,390
And they place them there at eye level for a six-year-old,

110
00:08:51,790 --> 00:08:55,930
just so they can pester you for the next seven minutes.

111
00:08:56,510 --> 00:08:58,770
Daddy, look at this. Daddy, how about this?

112
00:08:58,970 --> 00:09:00,570
Can we smell this? Can we taste this?

113
00:09:00,570 --> 00:09:03,830
Can we try this? How about this? On and on and on.

114
00:09:05,390 --> 00:09:10,290
I don't intend to go into the store to buy gum or Snickers or Milky Way.

115
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:13,470
And I'm pretty good, actually, about saying no.

116
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:16,900
But it's sometimes in my own weakness.

117
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:21,200
Oh, just one. And we plop it there.

118
00:09:21,820 --> 00:09:27,040
And it rides the little belt, and we ring it up, and it's 65 cents or 95 cents.

119
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:30,480
It's really no big deal in the big picture.

120
00:09:32,190 --> 00:09:34,110
It's just a couple of bucks.

121
00:09:35,430 --> 00:09:37,350
But you know, I got some statistics I heard

122
00:09:37,350 --> 00:09:44,760
that Americans spend $2.5 billion for chewing gum a year.

123
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:47,290
It's just a couple of bucks.

124
00:09:48,330 --> 00:09:49,930
But it adds up, doesn't it?

125
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:55,860
$2.9 billion is spent in arcade games in our country.

126
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:58,660
$12 billion on candy.

127
00:10:00,790 --> 00:10:03,910
And only $1.7 billion on worldwide evangelism.

128
00:10:04,710 --> 00:10:08,710
You can see the disparity in spending in our country.

129
00:10:09,530 --> 00:10:12,350
How much do you have in your budget for chewing gum this coming year?

130
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:19,670
I don't budget for chewing gum, but I spend on it sometimes.

131
00:10:22,010 --> 00:10:25,910
At the checkout counter, let's be honest, we spend extra with no forethought.

132
00:10:26,170 --> 00:10:28,650
And it's easy sometimes to do that in our church.

133
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:33,430
We can look in our wallet that week, and if there's 50 bucks, we can tithe right out of our wallet.

134
00:10:33,690 --> 00:10:35,050
Well, Lord, here's your five.

135
00:10:35,050 --> 00:10:38,400
and we can give God a tip

136
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,940
with no forethought

137
00:10:40,940 --> 00:10:44,270
or perhaps if the service was pretty good,

138
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:48,020
we'll give God a decent tip that week.

139
00:10:49,420 --> 00:10:52,420
Maybe I should put the offering after the sermon every week.

140
00:10:53,460 --> 00:10:55,260
Might get a few more tips, I don't know.

141
00:10:57,510 --> 00:10:59,630
But God, friends, doesn't want our tip.

142
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:02,500
He wants our intentional giving

143
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:05,400
as an act of holy worship.

144
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:07,320
Holy worship.

145
00:11:09,110 --> 00:11:14,370
He wants it intentional with joy as an offering made unto the Lord

146
00:11:14,370 --> 00:11:19,070
because it's holy and it's His as an act of worship.

147
00:11:20,650 --> 00:11:22,130
And here's what that might look like.

148
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:24,330
And I'm challenged.

149
00:11:24,470 --> 00:11:26,870
I don't do this, but I need to.

150
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:32,940
Do you receive your paycheck and thank God for the ability to earn it,

151
00:11:32,940 --> 00:11:37,640
for the ability to use the gifts and the talents that you have

152
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:40,000
to make the money that you've brought in

153
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,760
and then thank the Lord for the goodness

154
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:44,700
of having a job to begin with

155
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:46,790
and then take that check

156
00:11:46,790 --> 00:11:49,290
and with gladness say,

157
00:11:49,290 --> 00:11:50,410
Lord, thank you.

158
00:11:53,860 --> 00:11:54,900
And wouldn't it be great

159
00:11:54,900 --> 00:11:56,880
if we all with an attitude of gratitude

160
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,900
each and every pay period said,

161
00:11:59,000 --> 00:11:59,920
Lord, thank you

162
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,840
and moved the decimal place over

163
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:04,440
and gave unto the Lord the first fruits

164
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:06,340
as an act of worship.

165
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:09,260
Can you imagine what that would do

166
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:10,620
to our life of our church

167
00:12:10,620 --> 00:12:14,440
and to our own hearts each and every week or two weeks

168
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:17,640
or once a month, however it comes to you.

169
00:12:19,580 --> 00:12:21,480
Will we take God at his word?

170
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:28,430
Will we trust him with our lives and our giving?

171
00:12:30,100 --> 00:12:31,720
The first issue is treasure.

172
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:34,600
The second one has to do with trust.

173
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:38,300
Now back to that checkout counter.

174
00:12:40,110 --> 00:12:42,070
How many of you, I don't have to raise your hands,

175
00:12:42,070 --> 00:12:45,870
but how many this week have read the National Enquirer?

176
00:12:46,630 --> 00:12:48,130
Inquiring minds want to know, you know?

177
00:12:48,230 --> 00:12:50,340
I mean, not a lot of you.

178
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:51,080
All right, well, fair enough.

179
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,220
There's maybe not a lot of truth there.

180
00:12:54,310 --> 00:12:55,870
It might be interesting reading.

181
00:12:55,950 --> 00:13:01,120
It might bring a smile to your face, but it's probably not really true.

182
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,220
I haven't seen a lot of alien babies lately.

183
00:13:03,220 --> 00:13:04,560
I don't know.

184
00:13:04,780 --> 00:13:09,040
You'd think you'd see more, given how every week there seems to be a new one born.

185
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:10,920
Just a thought.

186
00:13:11,860 --> 00:13:13,080
Maybe People magazine.

187
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:17,960
More truth, but you know, probably not all true.

188
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:21,990
What about the Bible?

189
00:13:23,860 --> 00:13:25,760
Did we read the Scripture this week?

190
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:28,700
That is 100% true.

191
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:30,400
All of it.

192
00:13:31,910 --> 00:13:36,290
And do we believe it and live it and live it out in our lives?

193
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:42,180
2,000 verses about money that challenge us from different perspectives.

194
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:45,760
And it's God's perspective on our treasure.

195
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:49,000
Do we know what it is and do we live it out?

196
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:53,940
I want to share one of the most challenging to me and eye-popping verses

197
00:13:53,940 --> 00:13:57,460
about tithing and giving that's in the Scripture.

198
00:13:58,080 --> 00:14:00,860
We've studied it before, but I share it again for us.

199
00:14:00,860 --> 00:14:06,720
From Malachi chapter 3, the word is,

200
00:14:06,980 --> 00:14:10,460
I am the Lord, and I do not change.

201
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:17,900
That is why you descendants of Jacob are not already completely destroyed.

202
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:21,440
Ever since the days of your ancestors,

203
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:25,480
You have scorned my laws and failed to obey them.

204
00:14:26,100 --> 00:14:33,680
Now return to me, and I will return to you, says the Lord Almighty.

205
00:14:35,670 --> 00:14:40,080
But you ask, how can we return when we have never gone away?

206
00:14:41,260 --> 00:14:42,760
Should people cheat God?

207
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:45,160
Yet you have cheated me.

208
00:14:46,470 --> 00:14:48,130
But you ask, what do you mean?

209
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:50,620
When did we ever cheat you?

210
00:14:50,620 --> 00:14:55,500
You have cheated me of the tithes and the offerings due to me.

211
00:14:55,820 --> 00:15:00,020
You are under a curse, for your whole nation has been cheating me.

212
00:15:00,580 --> 00:15:05,460
Bring all the tithes into the storehouse, so there will be enough food in my temple.

213
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:12,410
And if you do, says the Lord Almighty, I will open the windows of heaven for you.

214
00:15:12,690 --> 00:15:17,970
I will pour out a blessing so great, you won't have enough room to take it in.

215
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:22,660
Try it. Let me prove it to you.

216
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:28,600
Your crops will be abundant, for I will guard them from insects and disease.

217
00:15:29,570 --> 00:15:35,340
Your grapes will not shrivel before they are ripe, says the Lord Almighty.

218
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:44,220
Then all the nations will call you blessed, for your land will be such a delight, says the Lord Almighty.

219
00:15:44,660 --> 00:15:49,140
God is speaking to the nation of Israel.

220
00:15:49,140 --> 00:15:56,420
A people at the time of the writing that had grown cold in their love and their worship of the Lord.

221
00:15:57,380 --> 00:15:59,560
They were more interested in other things.

222
00:16:00,660 --> 00:16:04,080
They were more interested in pursuing other interests.

223
00:16:04,420 --> 00:16:06,240
They didn't make time for God.

224
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:11,130
And they didn't give God the first fruits of what he had given to them.

225
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:18,420
We know that where our treasure is, there our hearts will be also.

226
00:16:18,420 --> 00:16:22,360
And in this setting, the people's hearts were far from God,

227
00:16:22,540 --> 00:16:24,820
and God wanted their hearts.

228
00:16:25,910 --> 00:16:29,410
Most of all, He wants our hearts.

229
00:16:29,690 --> 00:16:34,750
He's always wanted our hearts, and today He wants your hearts.

230
00:16:38,020 --> 00:16:41,880
Where we put our treasure, that's where our heart goes.

231
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:47,160
And God asks us to give the first tenth of our income,

232
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:51,760
and the Scriptures say the first tenth is holy and belongs to the Lord.

233
00:16:51,940 --> 00:16:59,980
But it's hard. It's really hard, isn't it, to give that first tenth.

234
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:03,920
It is really hard to give the first tenth.

235
00:17:04,020 --> 00:17:06,600
I know. I struggled for years.

236
00:17:08,390 --> 00:17:11,390
It's a lot easier to give the last tenth, isn't it?

237
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:18,520
After the bills are paid and all the fun has been expended and all the good things have been done,

238
00:17:18,980 --> 00:17:26,010
it's a lot easier to give when there's some leftover, if there's anything at all.

239
00:17:26,010 --> 00:17:31,410
But the first tenth, that's hard.

240
00:17:32,340 --> 00:17:33,300
That's a sacrifice.

241
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:34,880
That's really intentional.

242
